<span id="freeTextContainer1191781648847698842">Ebola&apos;s back. Want to know how it all started? Read this book. If you&apos;re not terrified by the time you&apos;re done, you&apos;re not paying attention or you have far too much faith in the strength of man versus microbes. I read this for a graduate-level history class on &quot;Ecology, Disease, and Population&quot;. Needless to say, we spent quite a bit of time studying how disease has shaped human history.</span>
  <span id="freeText1191781648847698842" style="display:none">Ebola's back. Want to know how it all started? Read this book. If you're not terrified by the time you're done, you're not paying attention or you have far too much faith in the strength of man versus microbes. I read this for a graduate-level history class on "Ecology, Disease, and Population". Needless to say, we spent quite a bit of time studying how disease has shaped human history.</span>
