<span id="freeTextContainer1316002270443238581">This is the best book you can read about disease, and it was the best thing I read in library school. Seriously, all of library school. You can just imagine how many books you have to read for something called &quot;library school.&quot;<br/><br/>Probably a more important read than ever, the Coming Plague talks quite a bit about Ebola, for one, and the different methods by which diseases can be fought, how difficult it is to eradicate a disease, and how often politics and science can&apos;t get on the same page.<br/><br/>Don&apos;t lo</span>
  <span id="freeText1316002270443238581" style="display:none">This is the best book you can read about disease, and it was the best thing I read in library school. Seriously, all of library school. You can just imagine how many books you have to read for something called "library school."<br /><br />Probably a more important read than ever, the Coming Plague talks quite a bit about Ebola, for one, and the different methods by which diseases can be fought, how difficult it is to eradicate a disease, and how often politics and science can't get on the same page.<br /><br />Don't look at the number of pages. Just pick it up and start. I promise, you will not be bored.</span>
